{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cfa97fb8-9674-4396-a8e1-5ffe933adec8","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the CLI flags change. The equivalent command is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** in your test project:\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` (enables `dotnet test` integration)\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\nEverything after `--` is passed directly to the test platform runner, bypassing the VSTest adapter layer.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"05e39bf9-3cc2-4e13-afe6-7d2c466918af","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` (with Microsoft.CodeCoverage) or you use a different approach\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout` map to `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nWith the new test platform, you can still use `dotnet test` and pass arguments after `--`, or invoke the test executable directly. The integration has evolved across .NET versions, so the exact approach depends on your setup.\n\nThe flag mappings are shifting too: `--filter` becomes `--treenode-filter` or stays as `--filter` depending on the test framework, `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`, code coverage moves to `--coverage` with format options, and crash/hang diagnostics use `--crashdump` and `--hangdump` respectively.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform in .NET 8, I can either run the test project directly with `dotnet run` and pass arguments after `--`, or use `dotnet test` with the `--` separator to forward arguments to the platform. I need to clarify which approach is more standard here.\n\nThe filter syntax is different too—instead of `Category=Integration`, I'd use the tree node filter format like `--treenode-filter \"/**[Category=Integration]\"`. For coverage, crash dumps, and hang dumps, each requires its own NuGet package (`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`), and TRX reporting needs the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` package.","outputTokens":1290,"requestId":"480B:112B3A:2F192FC:33BA3FB:69FBE37A"},"id":"bece2df1-d971-4dd2-8924-07c93ee7dde5","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:57:54.340Z","parentId":"75210aa1-d092-423a-b923-e2d6a2bb94cc"}
